    "title": "Hiring Medical Officer at Stryker India South Asia Partners",
    "description": "We at Stryker India South Asia Partners are looking for an experienced Medical Officer based out of Vijayawada. If you are a result-oriented professional with a passion for excellence, we want to hear from you.\n\nAbout Stryker India South Asia Partners:\nStryker India South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Sc / M.Sc in Life Sciences\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Learning & development budget\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Flexible working hours\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Vijayawada, Andhra Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Stryker India South Asia Partners!",
